[{"id":"VR788177","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a diagram of an apparatus divided into two regions: a region labeled “Ion Source” to the left, and a region labeled “Region of Uniform Electric Field” to the right. In the Ion Source region, the left end is labeled “Ions Created Here,” and a horizontal dashed line is drawn through the middle of the region with arrows along it that point to the right. An arrow pointing to the right below the region is labeled delta uppercase V equals negative uppercase V sub 0. In the Region of Uniform Electric Field, the height of the region is given as d, and vertically downward pointing arrows fill the region. The dashed line from the Ion Source region curves downward and to the right as it enters the Region of Uniform Electric Field, and intersects the bottom of the region at a point labeled P.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR788177.g01.svg\"/></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">The figure shows an apparatus that consists of an ion source on the left and a region of uniform electric field on the right. In the ion source, ions of mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"M\"><math alttext=\"M\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>M</mi></math></span></span> and charge <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive e\"><math alttext=\"positive e\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mo>+</mo><mi>e</mi></math></span></span> are created at the far left end, accelerate from rest through a potential difference <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"negative uppercase V sub 0\"><math alttext=\"negative uppercase V sub 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mpadded><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>V</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mpadded></math></span></span>, and exit the source. The ions then move a short distance at a constant velocity from the source into the region of uniform electric field. In this region, the electric field is downward and has magnitude <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the magnitude of vector E, equals the fraction with numerator uppercase V sub 0, and denominator d\"><math alttext=\"the magnitude of vector E, equals the fraction with numerator uppercase V sub 0, and denominator d\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mrow><mo>|</mo><mover accent=\"true\"><mi>E</mi><mo>→</mo></mover><mo>|</mo></mrow><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>V</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mi>d</mi></mfrac></math></span></span>, where <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"d\"><math alttext=\"d\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>d</mi></math></span></span> is the distance between the top and bottom of the uniform field region. The ions enter this region halfway between the top and the bottom of the region, are deflected downward by the field, and reach the bottom of the region at Point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"P\"><math alttext=\"P\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi></math></span></span>, as indicated. What is the speed of the ions when they reach Point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"P\"><math alttext=\"P\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi></math></span></span>?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR788177_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the square root of the fraction with numerator 2 e times uppercase V sub 0, and denominator M, end root\"><math alttext=\"the square root of the fraction with numerator 2 e times uppercase V sub 0, and denominator M, end root\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>e</mi><msub><mi>V</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mrow><mi>M</mi></mfrac></msqrt></mstyle></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the square root of the fraction with numerator 3 e times uppercase V sub 0, and denominator M, end root\"><math alttext=\"the square root of the fraction with numerator 3 e times uppercase V sub 0, and denominator M, end root\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>e</mi><msub><mi>V</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mrow><mi>M</mi></mfrac></msqrt></mstyle></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the square root of the fraction with numerator 4 e times uppercase V sub 0, and denominator M, end root\"><math alttext=\"the square root of the fraction with numerator 4 e times uppercase V sub 0, and denominator M, end root\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>e</mi><msub><mi>V</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mrow><mi>M</mi></mfrac></msqrt></mstyle></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the square root of the fraction with numerator, the square root of 5, end root, times e times uppercase V sub 0, and denominator M, end root\"><math alttext=\"the square root of the fraction with numerator, the square root of 5, end root, times e times uppercase V sub 0, and denominator M, end root\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><msqrt><mn>5</mn></msqrt><mi>e</mi><msub><mi>V</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mrow><mi>M</mi></mfrac></msqrt></mstyle></math></span></span></p>"],"answer":1}]